<item>
            <title>[LU-10555] e2fsprog misnamed el7 for latest el6 release</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10555</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like the latest x86_64 RPMs for e2fsprogs on el6 are misnamed.  When I browse to &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/e2fsprogs/latest/el6/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/e2fsprogs/latest/el6/RPMS/x86_64/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see RPMs with .el7 in the name.  Looking at the RPM fields in one of th RPMs I see that it claims to have been built on an el6 machine&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  trevis-306-el6-x8664-2.trevis.hpdd.intel.com&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but from an el7 source RPM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  e2fsprogs-1.42.13.wc6-7.el7.src.rpm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know if this is just a simple misnaming or if the wrong source RPM was used but it is a bit confusing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
